Allow non-root users to obtain the system serial number, which on some
platforms can only be obtain via dmidecode. As dmidecode accesses
kernel memory for some information, it can only be run by root. This
unfortunately means that none of the information it provides can be
obtained without root privileges.

System-serial-number uses SUID to run

	dmidecode -s system-serial-number.

It does not allow the user to obtain other information via dmidecode.

System-serial-number must be installed by the root user, but may then
be used by anyone.
